<h4>DISINTEGRATION LOOPS — 2001</h4>
<p>In 2001, William Basinski discovered tapes he had made in the 1980s were disintegrating as he digitized them. The oxide was falling off the tape — the music was literally erasing itself during playback. He recorded the process. The result was played on a rooftop in Brooklyn on September 11, 2001, as smoke rose over Manhattan. It became one of the most important works of art of the 21st century.</p>
